Why vendored
------------
The frozen-backbone G2G pose-estimation module needs the multi-view
information-sharing features that MapAnything computes *before* its DPT
prediction head. Upstream v1.0.1 does not expose these features, so a single
small modification is applied (below). The package is vendored here so the
release is self-contained and reproduces the exact backbone used for training
and evaluation.

Modifications relative to upstream v1.0.1
-----------------------------------------
Exactly ONE source file differs from upstream v1.0.1; every other file is
byte-for-byte identical:

  mapanything/models/mapanything/model.py
    `MapAnything.forward()` gains an optional argument
    `return_info_sharing_features` (default False). When True, forward()
    early-returns the multi-view information-sharing features (before the DPT
    prediction head) as a list of [B, C, H_patch, W_patch] tensors. This is
    the feature interface consumed by
    `g2g/models/stage2_model_multiframe.py`.

When `return_info_sharing_features` is False (the default), behavior is
identical to upstream v1.0.1.
